# LLM Request Policy

## Context policy
- Keep every LLM call under 12k estimated input tokens when possible.
- Never read extra files beyond the explicit read-set.
- Ignore prior responses/tools. Fresh context only.
- Prefer 3-5 files max per call; for routine tasks prefer 2-3.

## Large-file rules
- Never include full contents of large files.
- Large Python modules: use signatures only, imports only, or 1-2 selected blocks.
- Large tests: include only relevant test cases / fixtures / assertions pattern.
- Large docs: include only the relevant section, status table, last entry, or short summary.

## Forbidden full-read files
SSoT: `doc/token_safety_registry.json`. Check before reading:
`python scripts/check_readset.py <file>...` — SAFE / WARN / BLOCK.

## Compression rule
- > 12k tokens — compress (trim history, use signatures/sections, drop low-signal files).
- > 20k tokens — stop and report blocker. Max 1 retry after compression.